s to god the company vision was supplied by god in september  i received a vision and a mandate manage the energy resources of the earth according to god’s design take a moment to imagine what god’s intended design for energy resources would be if we would just follow god’s mandate to use the resources properly it would lead to peace and prosperity today we are running out of low cost petroleum it is a finite resource because most oil is produced in areas of the world that are politically unstable at best and dangerous at worst the usa spends billions of dollars a year protecting supply with its military because the world is growing economically the demand for more oil is outstripping supply so competition is increasing and nonindigenous oil producing nations are spending more of their gdp on energy this is destroying the ability of nations to grow and for their populations to feed themselves yet most countries that don’t produce oil are agrarian based by redirecting the agricultural model in these countries by increasing food production and creating an energy resource crop to offset their oil imports it keeps more of the countries gdp incountry for economic development the key to economic growth is to create a consumer base this can only be accomplished when the population has money to buy consumables beyond food that requires jobs and industry bluefire does all these things by first creating a supply chain for feedstock to its production plants by enabling farmers to grow energy crops that also produce food and can be used for export beyond internal consumption second by producing a compatible transportation fuel for the country from the feedstock it offsets capital that flows out of the country to buy oil thereby keeping the money in country for industrial development third bluefire can produce chemicals beyond fuels that would create the feedstock for the next industry like biodisposable plastics or food additives like citric acid in the garden of eden it was all about agrarian growth let’s go back to god’s model at bluefire we believe that the company’s purpose is to create the opportunities for change that can make a difference in the lives and economies of nations through the deployment of technologies that can be low tech yet at the same time create new opportunities for the indigenous population by giving farmers and the lowest economic level of the population the opportunity to earn more money and increase personal productivity leads to the increase for the whole nation bluefire changes the paradigm from a petro based econometric model to an agrarian based econometric model and the possibilities for the nation are endless just like god had originally intended the countries are no longer held hostage to oil bluefire’s nearterm mission is to free the us from the turmoil and crisis of being held hostage by oil producing nations our longterm mission is to improve the living conditions of impoverished people in the developing world i have participated in mission trips and have ministered to families living in waste dumps in places like tepic nargarit mexico the philippines indonesia and elsewhere as a pastor and graduate of cottonwood leadership college i see the vision and have the heart to help and change the conditions of the people society values the least bluefire’s technology deployment will immediately improve their living conditions through employment and at the same time we will create a sustainable econometric model to lift them out of the dumps–literally–and help them break free of economic bondage and the spiritual oppression that comes with it my decisions and actions are guided by god my primary job is to ensure that the investment made in the company is put to the best possible use to grow the company and manage its success this includes the investment of hard work and creativity from the team of people that work for the company the investment of prayer from those who believe in us and are committed to our success and the investment of those who finance the company this is a huge responsibility to prepare myself for this responsibility i completed the program at cottonwood christian leadership college this training prepared me to make decisions based on biblical principles and minister to those who seek to establish a closer relationship with god all the glory goes to god our team is very experienced and has been successful in commercializing technologies and running companies in the past but it is god that uses us and gives this company success as senior management and employees of bluefire we see ourselves as god’s agents here on earth to implement his vision and achieve his growth plan god is the true builder of this company and our security growth and success are because of him for more power go to wwwrealpowertodaycom bluefire approach fulton construction progress production plant our technology investor center real power archives february  october  october  february  december  november  june  march  january  november  october  september  june  news the exportimport bank of china renews letter of intent to bluefire renewables for fulton project due diligence continues to reach a financial closing bluefire’s fulton project receives strong endorsement in china’s portfolio of projects presented at the uschina joint commission on commerce and trade bluefire renewables receives unprecedented exportimport bank of china letter of intent to provide debt financing for a us bioenergy project navigation about news contact links bluefire approach production plant our technology investor center real power fulton construction progress our location  musick irvine ca  main  fax  email inquiriesbfreinccom   bluefire renewables all the respective rights reserved website  apps free android apps download apps  jasa seo jakarta bluefire renewables   links home about news fulton construction progress contact links links  resources clean fuels development coalition governor schwarzeneg