nse the arkenol technology that converts cellulose and waste materials into ethanol and other high value chemicals it also focuses on providing professional services to biorefineries worldwide the company was formerly known as bluefire ethanol fuels inc and changed its name to bluefire renewables inc in july  bluefire renewables inc was founded in  and is based in mission viejo california detailed description  marguerite parkwaysuite amission viejo ca united statesfounded in  employees phone  wwwbluefireethanolcom key executives for bluefire renewables inc mr arnold r klann chairman chief executive officer president  cfo age  total annual compensation k mr john e cuzens chief technology officer age  total annual compensation k compensation as of fiscal year  bluefire renewables inc key developments bluefire renewables inc announced delayed q filing may   on  bluefire renewables inc announced that they will be unable to file their next q by the deadline required by the sec bluefire renewables inc announced delayed annual k filing mar   on  bluefire renewables inc announced that they will be unable to file their next k by the deadline required by the sec bluefire renewables inc announces resignation of ms necitas sumait as member of the board of directors jan   bluefire renewables inc announced that ms necitas sumait resigned as a member of the board of directors of the company effective immediately similar private companies by industry company name region  oil wells in east texas field united states  good energy inc united states  horizons llc united states  energy holdings llc united states  fields in williston basin united states recent private companies transactions typedate target no transactions available in the past  months request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquiries please contact sp 